# Spacecraft AI backend — LLM configuration (item 15, NPC greetings).
# Copy to ".env" and fill in. With no model/base URL set, the backend uses a deterministic
# bilingual template (so it works with zero setup); set these to enable a real LLM.
#
# Everything goes through the OpenAI-compatible chat API, so pick ONE provider below.

# --- Option A: LM Studio (self-hosted, no key needed) ---
# SPACECRAFT_AI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1
# SPACECRAFT_AI_MODEL=local-model            # whatever model id LM Studio is serving
# SPACECRAFT_AI_API_KEY=lm-studio            # ignored by LM Studio, any value is fine

# --- Option B: OpenAI ---
# SPACECRAFT_AI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# SPACECRAFT_AI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# SPACECRAFT_AI_API_KEY=sk-...

# --- Option C: Claude (Anthropic, OpenAI-compatible endpoint) ---
# SPACECRAFT_AI_BASE_URL=https://api.anthropic.com/v1/
# SPACECRAFT_AI_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# SPACECRAFT_AI_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Sampling (optional)
# SPACECRAFT_AI_TEMPERATURE=0.8
